abstract: Before reports of the latest quake, Wall Street shares had edged higher, spurred by reports that fewer people applied for unemployment benefits and that retailers showed stronger sales.
snippet: Before reports of the latest quake, Wall Street shares had edged higher, spurred by reports that fewer people applied for unemployment benefits and that retailers showed stronger sales.
lead_paragraph: Oil prices rose to their highest level in more than two years on Thursday, while Wall Street erased gains prompted by better-than-expected economic data after reports of another earthquake in Japan.

headline.main: Markets Turn Lower, and Oil Prices Rise Again
headline.print_headline:
Markets Turn Lower,
And Oil Prices Rise Again
